## D-04 · Agent Pattern — Supervisor-Routed over Monolithic Prompt

**Decision:** Use a SupervisorAgent that decides which specialist agents to invoke per PR,
rather than running all agents on every PR or using a single mega-prompt.

**Context:** A single prompt covering security + perf + arch + tests would be 8k+ tokens
of system prompt, produce unfocused output, and hallucinate across domains. Running all
agents unconditionally wastes tokens on PRs where only one domain is relevant (e.g., a
pure CSS change doesn't need SecurityAgent).

**Alternatives considered:**

- Single monolithic prompt — simpler but lower quality; harder to tune per domain
- Always-run all 4 agents sequentially — deterministic but wasteful; ~4x token cost
- User-configurable fixed agent set — useful but doesn't use diff content to decide

**Rejected because:** Supervisor routing is the core differentiator. It reads diff
metadata (file types, paths, change volume) and makes an informed routing decision,
avoiding wasted tokens and improving per-domain focus.

---

## D-05 · Agent Framework — LangGraph OSS over LangChain AgentExecutor / Custom

**Decision:** Use LangGraph OSS (StateGraph) for the multi-agent pipeline orchestration.

**Context:** The pipeline has branching logic (supervisor decides routes), shared state
(findings accumulated across agents), and needs deterministic execution order.

**Alternatives considered:**

- LangChain AgentExecutor — opaque tool loop; hard to inspect intermediate state
- LangGraph Cloud — same as OSS but managed; paid service
- Custom Python orchestration — full control but rebuilds what LangGraph provides

**Rejected because:** LangGraph OSS gives a stateful, inspectable graph with typed state
(ReviewState TypedDict), conditional edges, and native Langfuse tracing integration — all
for free. Cloud version is unnecessary for self-hosted deployment.

---

## D-06 · Observability — Langfuse over LangSmith

**Decision:** Use Langfuse Cloud (free tier) for LLM tracing, span-level token tracking,
and evaluation datasets.

**Context:** Need per-agent traces, token usage, latency, and eval scoring against a
golden set of known-bad PRs.

**Alternatives considered:**

- LangSmith — 1,500 traces/month on free tier; not enough at any review volume
- OpenTelemetry — no LLM-specific spans; requires custom instrumentation per model call
- Helicone — good for proxy-based logging; less suited for multi-agent eval datasets

**Rejected because:** LangSmith's free tier is too restrictive. Langfuse has 50k events/
month free, built-in dataset + eval UI, and a LangGraph integration. Open-source so
self-hostable if needed.

