## D-07 · GitHub Integration — GitHub App over OAuth App / PAT

**Decision:** Use a GitHub App for all GitHub integration (webhooks, API calls, comment posting).

**Context:** Need webhooks per-repo, higher rate limits, and the ability to work across
multiple orgs without user OAuth sessions.

**Alternatives considered:**

- GitHub OAuth App — requires user to be logged in for all API calls; lower rate limits
- Personal Access Token — user-specific; doesn't scale; no webhook support at org level
- GitHub Actions integration — only works inside CI; can't receive PR events externally

**Rejected because:** GitHub App gives a dedicated bot identity, per-installation access
tokens (5,000 req/hour vs 60 for unauthenticated), and webhook delivery at the org/repo
level without requiring individual user OAuth sessions.

