## D-08 · Backend Architecture — Clean Architecture over Simple Layered

**Decision:** Use Clean Architecture (Domain / Application / Infrastructure / API) rather
than a flat routes → services → repositories → DB structure.

**Context:** This project has 3 swappable external systems (GitHub→GitLab in EX-07,
vector DB, queue), is designed to go multi-tenant (EX-01), and needs strong unit
testability without spinning up infrastructure.

**Alternatives considered:**

- Simple layered (routes/services/repos/db) — less boilerplate; familiar from Node
- Hexagonal (ports & adapters) — equivalent pattern, different terminology

**Rejected because:** Simple layers don't enforce interface isolation — services can
directly import SQLAlchemy or the GitHub client, making swaps painful. Clean Architecture
enforces the dependency rule at the import level. Hexagonal is equivalent; we chose Clean
Architecture for naming clarity.

**Trade-off acknowledged:** ~20–30% more boilerplate upfront. Justified by EX-01 and
EX-07 extensibility goals.

