## D-11 · Diff Handling — Hybrid (Full / Per-File) over Always-Chunk / RAG-Only

**Decision:** Pass the full unified diff when PR has ≤50 changed files; chunk per-file
for larger PRs. Use RAG for broader codebase context in both modes.

**Context:** Gemini 2.5 Flash has a 1M token context window, but system prompts, few-shot
examples, RAG chunks, and per-agent instructions together consume 8–15k tokens. For large
PRs, the diff itself can exceed 200k tokens.

**Alternatives considered:**

- Always chunk per-file — loses cross-file context (e.g., a function moved between files)
- Always full diff — hits context limits on PRs with 100+ files
- RAG-only (embed diff, retrieve top-k) — loses sequential diff structure and line numbers

**Rejected because:** Always-chunk and RAG-only both lose important cross-file signals.
Hybrid gives full context for typical PRs (≤50 files) and degrades gracefully for large ones.

**50-file threshold:** Conservative estimate based on ~2k tokens per changed file average.
Revisit if real-world token counts differ significantly.

