## D-13 · Embedding Scope — Selective Per-PR (not full codebase snapshot)

**Decision:** Embed only the files touched by the PR (changed files + their 1-hop import
graph) rather than indexing the entire repository upfront.

**Context:** A large repository may have 10,000+ files. Embedding the full codebase
upfront wastes Gemini embedding quota (1,500 RPD free), storage, and latency. The context
relevant to any specific PR is bounded by what that PR touches.

**Alternatives considered:**

- Full codebase index — comprehensive but expensive, stale between PRs, hits free-tier limits
- Diff-only embedding — cheap but loses cross-file context (callers, imports, type definitions)
- No embeddings — agents have no retrieval; false positive rate increases

**Rejected because:** Full indexing wastes the free-tier quota on files irrelevant to the
PR. Diff-only loses cross-file context. Selective embedding gives the right balance.

**Cleanup strategy:** On `pull_request.closed` (merged or closed), delete all
`code_embeddings` rows for `(repository_id, head_sha)`. Belt-and-suspenders: a weekly
background job deletes rows older than 30 days to handle missed webhooks.

**Edge case:** If two PRs share a head SHA (cherry-pick scenario), the cleanup of one
deletes the other's embeddings. Accepted for MVP — embeddings are re-created on next review.

