## D-14 · Review Trigger — Every `synchronize` Event (full base→head diff)

**Decision:** Trigger a full review on `opened`, `synchronize`, and `reopened` events.
Each review covers the full PR diff (base_sha → head_sha), not just the incremental push.

**Context:** Authors push follow-up commits after receiving feedback. A reviewer who only
sees the first version is useless in the iterative cycle.

**Alternatives considered:**

- Only on `opened` — misses follow-up reviews; reduces tool value to one-shot feedback
- Only on significant pushes (debounced) — adds complexity; hard to define "significant"
- On `merged` only — too late for the author to act on findings

**Rejected because:** Review value is highest during the open PR lifecycle. Reviewing
only on open makes the tool a linter, not a reviewer.

**Rapid-push behaviour:** Multiple pushes in quick succession queue multiple jobs. For
MVP, this is accepted (extra jobs are harmless). A future improvement: if a new job for
the same PR arrives while a previous one is `pending`, cancel the older one.

**What "full diff" means:** Always diff base_sha → head_sha (the full PR, not the
incremental push delta). This ensures agents see the complete change set in context.

